WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.547 --> 00:00:05.050
[crickets chirping]

2
00:00:16.863 --> 00:00:19.898
[water running]

3
00:00:20.031 --> 00:00:23.669
[heavy fast breathing]

4
00:00:31.411 --> 00:00:32.578
Fuck!

5
00:00:42.889 --> 00:00:46.091
[eerie music intensifies]

6
00:00:47.860 --> 00:00:49.995
[Marshall] <i>It's not</i>
<i>the blood you can't wash out</i>


7
00:00:50.128 --> 00:00:51.631
<i>you should worry about.</i>

8
00:00:59.271 --> 00:01:01.139
<i>It's the blood you can.</i>

9
00:01:04.710 --> 00:01:08.213
[tense music playing]

10
00:01:13.285 --> 00:01:14.554
Everything all right?

11
00:01:17.390 --> 00:01:20.091
Yeah. I'm fine.
Fine. Why?


12
00:01:21.894 --> 00:01:24.630
You get all that blood
off your hands preacher?


13
00:01:28.133 --> 00:01:29.569
[scoffs]

14
00:01:34.607 --> 00:01:36.208
[door clicks]

15
00:01:36.809 --> 00:01:39.978
[breathing heavily]

16
00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:43.916
[pensive music playing]

17
00:01:44.049 --> 00:01:47.520
[raindrops falling]

18
00:01:52.959 --> 00:01:54.660
[sniffles]

19
00:01:59.164 --> 00:02:02.100
[thunder rumbling]

20
00:02:02.234 --> 00:02:05.003
[sniffling]

21
00:02:08.908 --> 00:02:12.378
[cries softly]

22
00:02:12.512 --> 00:02:16.516
[pensive music continues]

23
00:02:18.651 --> 00:02:21.554
[rain pattering]

24
00:02:26.124 --> 00:02:28.628
[sniffling]

25
00:02:40.740 --> 00:02:43.442
[sighing]

26
00:02:49.015 --> 00:02:51.651
[paper rustling]

27
00:02:53.786 --> 00:02:55.788
[pen scratching]

28
00:03:06.632 --> 00:03:09.100
[cries]

29
00:03:27.386 --> 00:03:30.856
[music fades]

30
00:03:30.990 --> 00:03:34.259
[footsteps receding]

31
00:03:44.336 --> 00:03:47.238
Well, he isn't actually
gonna speak, is he?


32
00:03:49.107 --> 00:03:53.244
After all
his wife just died.


33
00:03:57.550 --> 00:04:01.854
I have, uh, pastored
most of y'all for 20 years.


34
00:04:04.090 --> 00:04:07.192
And, uh,
to be honest, I'm--


35
00:04:08.094 --> 00:04:09.395
I'm up here...

36
00:04:12.765 --> 00:04:14.900
because I don't know
how to do anything else.


37
00:04:19.137 --> 00:04:20.773
She was the best
part of me.


38
00:04:24.043 --> 00:04:25.444
Y'all know it, too.

39
00:04:26.211 --> 00:04:29.280
Half the time
you be clamoring


40
00:04:29.415 --> 00:04:31.584
to talk to her
after church and not me.


41
00:04:31.717 --> 00:04:33.386
[chuckles]

42
00:04:35.755 --> 00:04:39.825
I've spent
my whole life...


43
00:04:41.159 --> 00:04:42.862
waiting to talk to her.

44
00:04:47.066 --> 00:04:50.403
I guess I'll be waiting
a little longer still.


45
00:04:52.505 --> 00:04:54.272
[sniffs, clears throat]

46
00:04:56.542 --> 00:04:59.177
A lot of people
have asked me...


47
00:05:01.346 --> 00:05:05.350
what I think
of Troy Parker Junior...


48
00:05:06.852 --> 00:05:09.455
about whether
he deserves to pay


49
00:05:09.588 --> 00:05:12.725
for Elizabeth's life
with his own.


50
00:05:20.298 --> 00:05:22.200
Love your enemies.

51
00:05:24.904 --> 00:05:27.940
Pray for those
who hate you.


52
00:05:28.641 --> 00:05:32.111
Lord, forgive us
our sins as we forgive


53
00:05:32.243 --> 00:05:35.381
those who have sinned
against us.


54
00:05:37.616 --> 00:05:41.787
I believe there is
power in forgiveness.


55
00:05:41.921 --> 00:05:43.556
I have to believe that.

56
00:05:45.256 --> 00:05:47.660
Otherwise, my Jesus
is a liar.


57
00:05:49.628 --> 00:05:54.332
So I have talked
to the Texas district attorney


58
00:05:54.467 --> 00:05:58.771
and requested that
Mr. Parker's sentence...


59
00:06:00.406 --> 00:06:03.943
be fair and just...

60
00:06:05.444 --> 00:06:08.346
but also with
the possibility of parole...


61
00:06:11.117 --> 00:06:12.651
and redemption.

62
00:06:17.990 --> 00:06:19.391
[door creaking]

63
00:06:19.525 --> 00:06:22.394
[keys jangling]

64
00:06:24.430 --> 00:06:26.031
[door clicks]

65
00:06:29.668 --> 00:06:31.336
Hey, you want
dinner in a while?


66
00:06:32.303 --> 00:06:33.472
[door slams]

67
00:06:33.606 --> 00:06:37.409
[soft piano playing]

68
00:07:02.168 --> 00:07:04.069
Hey, you coming
down for dinner?


69
00:07:13.179 --> 00:07:14.446
Samuel?

70
00:07:16.682 --> 00:07:19.852
[thunder rumbling]

71
00:07:19.985 --> 00:07:22.888
[light rain]

72
00:07:28.794 --> 00:07:30.361
Samuel?

73
00:07:35.734 --> 00:07:38.604
[thunder rumbling]

74
00:07:48.414 --> 00:07:51.483
[music fades]

75
00:07:54.320 --> 00:07:57.022
[pensive music playing]

76
00:07:57.156 --> 00:08:00.259
[wind whooshing]

77
00:08:00.392 --> 00:08:03.095
[door buzzer sound]

78
00:08:11.537 --> 00:08:12.905
[Prison Guard] Parker!

79
00:08:14.573 --> 00:08:17.710
Parker! Troy!

80
00:08:19.411 --> 00:08:20.946
You coming or going?

81
00:08:26.619 --> 00:08:28.020
Bus will be
along any minute.


82
00:08:28.153 --> 00:08:31.590
[pensive music continues]

83
00:08:45.537 --> 00:08:48.173
[footsteps]

84
00:08:53.812 --> 00:08:57.750
[low piano music]

85
00:09:25.577 --> 00:09:28.447
[phone vibrates]

86
00:09:34.053 --> 00:09:36.488
[sighs]

87
00:09:36.622 --> 00:09:41.827
♪

88
00:09:58.844 --> 00:10:02.481
[indistinct chatter]

89
00:10:04.817 --> 00:10:06.852
Okay, so
if you come tomorrow--


90
00:10:06.986 --> 00:10:08.053
Samuel.

91
00:10:10.522 --> 00:10:12.091
Get in the car.

92
00:10:13.058 --> 00:10:14.626
[Samuel]
Am I in trouble or something?


93
00:10:14.760 --> 00:10:16.362
Why would you assume
you were in trouble?


94
00:10:16.495 --> 00:10:19.631
Because you haven't picked
me up since I was 13 years old.


95
00:10:24.103 --> 00:10:26.505
Troy Parker
is being released today.


96
00:10:28.874 --> 00:10:31.043
Mm. Five years, right?

97
00:10:32.311 --> 00:10:33.545
'Cause you wouldn't testify?

98
00:10:33.679 --> 00:10:35.047
It was
the right thing to do.


99
00:10:35.482 --> 00:10:38.684
Being a pastor don't make you
the expert on what's right.


100
00:10:43.456 --> 00:10:44.957
I just thought
you should know.


101
00:10:46.925 --> 00:10:48.495
Hey, can you gimme
a hand at the church tonight?


102
00:10:48.627 --> 00:10:49.928
[Samuel]
I got homework.


103
00:10:50.062 --> 00:10:51.464
Samuel, I can't do
everything myself.


104
00:10:51.597 --> 00:10:53.265
-[Samuel] Sorry.
-[car door shuts]


105
00:10:59.271 --> 00:11:01.540
[train honking]

106
00:11:01.974 --> 00:11:05.944
[soft music playing]

107
00:11:21.693 --> 00:11:24.663
[crickets chirping]

108
00:11:29.568 --> 00:11:31.270
You planning on
staying long?


109
00:11:31.703 --> 00:11:33.338
No, ma'am.

110
00:11:35.442 --> 00:11:37.342
[woman] Am I gonna
have trouble with you?


111
00:11:38.445 --> 00:11:39.711
No, ma'am.

112
00:11:43.483 --> 00:11:45.884
[soft whirring]

113
00:11:48.253 --> 00:11:50.355
[woman]
First, last, and security.


114
00:11:54.293 --> 00:11:56.595
That's just about
all I got.


115
00:11:57.629 --> 00:12:00.032
[money rustling]

116
00:12:11.043 --> 00:12:12.711
You always this welcoming?

117
00:12:15.047 --> 00:12:16.849
I know who you are.

118
00:12:20.686 --> 00:12:22.187
No smoking.

119
00:12:27.793 --> 00:12:29.361
[door clicks]

120
00:12:32.998 --> 00:12:37.604
[engine whirring]

121
00:12:37.736 --> 00:12:39.004
Sheriff's here.

122
00:12:40.839 --> 00:12:43.842
[gravel grinding]

123
00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:46.311
Maureen.

124
00:12:49.314 --> 00:12:51.150
Little early
in the day, ain't it Scott?


125
00:12:51.283 --> 00:12:52.818
[Scott] Come on.
You know what they say?


126
00:12:53.318 --> 00:12:55.154
You can take
the cop outta the big city.


127
00:12:55.287 --> 00:12:56.855
What happened?

128
00:12:57.856 --> 00:13:00.225
Was driving by,
saw the truck on fire.


129
00:13:00.359 --> 00:13:01.860
Local fire put it out.

130
00:13:04.464 --> 00:13:05.998
That's when they found--

131
00:13:09.435 --> 00:13:12.204
-Do we know who it is?
-Not yet.


132
00:13:13.338 --> 00:13:15.375
Coroner's on their way,

133
00:13:15.508 --> 00:13:18.110
-but they're in Paris and--
-And they drive slow.


134
00:13:18.243 --> 00:13:19.445
Molasses.

135
00:13:20.879 --> 00:13:22.214
Any guesses?

136
00:13:23.348 --> 00:13:25.117
Working theory,

137
00:13:25.250 --> 00:13:26.718
traveler passing through
for the night


138
00:13:26.852 --> 00:13:28.320
looking for
a place to stay.


139
00:13:29.221 --> 00:13:31.056
Doesn't explain
the gas though...


140
00:13:33.660 --> 00:13:35.060
or the tracks.

141
00:13:35.861 --> 00:13:37.196
[Scott]
Sorry, what's that?


142
00:13:38.096 --> 00:13:40.832
Well, sometimes pickup truck
uses different tires


143
00:13:40.966 --> 00:13:42.602
than a passenger car.

144
00:13:42.734 --> 00:13:45.370
That's a mid-eighties Ford
that's running on LT metrics.


145
00:13:45.505 --> 00:13:46.905
This is P.

146
00:13:49.642 --> 00:13:52.010
I always said it was
good for cops to have hobbies.


147
00:13:52.844 --> 00:13:54.313
That's why mine's origami.

148
00:13:54.947 --> 00:13:56.348
There was another car.

149
00:14:00.018 --> 00:14:02.054
Right. But, uh,
which means?


150
00:14:02.187 --> 00:14:03.489
This isn't
where it happened.


151
00:14:03.623 --> 00:14:07.059
[footsteps receding]

152
00:14:07.594 --> 00:14:08.727
Where are you going?

153
00:14:08.860 --> 00:14:09.895
To find out
where it did.


154
00:14:10.329 --> 00:14:12.164
Run the treads.
See where it takes us.


155
00:14:12.297 --> 00:14:13.466
Sure.

156
00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:16.368
I mean, I was gonna do that.
I just-- I--


157
00:14:17.403 --> 00:14:19.004
[engine revving]

158
00:14:19.137 --> 00:14:22.140
[crickets chirping]

159
00:14:42.894 --> 00:14:45.030
How was
the service pastor?


160
00:14:49.201 --> 00:14:51.504
I-- I probably
should have just called.


161
00:14:53.205 --> 00:14:54.840
I heard you got out.

162
00:14:55.742 --> 00:14:57.309
Yeah, just-- just yesterday.

163
00:15:00.345 --> 00:15:01.780
You came back.

164
00:15:04.417 --> 00:15:06.084
Did you hear
about my mom?


165
00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:09.254
No.

166
00:15:11.023 --> 00:15:12.858
Yeah, she, uh...

167
00:15:14.359 --> 00:15:15.495
she fell sick...

168
00:15:17.397 --> 00:15:19.565
a little over a year ago
and you know,


169
00:15:19.699 --> 00:15:24.136
I figured once I got out
I'd come back and help her out.


170
00:15:28.106 --> 00:15:29.575
You came by here.

171
00:15:37.750 --> 00:15:40.553
Look, you-- you didn't
have to do what you did.


172
00:15:42.287 --> 00:15:44.323
You know, about
my sentence and all.


173
00:15:47.760 --> 00:15:49.194
You're welcome.

174
00:15:55.768 --> 00:15:57.869
Yeah. All right.
[clears throat]


175
00:16:00.972 --> 00:16:02.274
Hey, Pastor.

176
00:16:03.275 --> 00:16:06.679
Hey, you-- you wouldn't
know anyone who'd, you know,


177
00:16:06.813 --> 00:16:08.581
hire an ex-con,
would you?


178
00:16:08.715 --> 00:16:10.282
Afraid not.

179
00:16:13.852 --> 00:16:15.455
Yeah, I didn't think so.

180
00:16:19.425 --> 00:16:21.360
Uh, I'll--
I'll let you be.


181
00:16:21.494 --> 00:16:22.462
Thank you, Pastor.

182
00:16:22.595 --> 00:16:26.064
[somber music playing]

183
00:16:29.769 --> 00:16:31.437
[door clicks]

184
00:16:37.275 --> 00:16:41.481
[labored breathing]

185
00:16:42.849 --> 00:16:44.650
[Troy]
Yes, sir. I'm here.


186
00:16:47.352 --> 00:16:49.888
No, sir, I'm not looking
to get into any trouble.


187
00:16:53.992 --> 00:16:55.327
No, sir.

188
00:16:55.927 --> 00:16:57.597
Got no plans
to leave the state.


189
00:17:00.700 --> 00:17:02.535
Uh, yes sir.

190
00:17:03.536 --> 00:17:04.637
Go ahead.

191
00:17:07.072 --> 00:17:08.441
Uh-huh.

192
00:17:12.545 --> 00:17:13.679
Yes, sir.

193
00:17:14.514 --> 00:17:15.681
Will do.

194
00:17:17.450 --> 00:17:18.618
Thank you, sir.

195
00:17:23.288 --> 00:17:24.990
My PO said
he called you?


196
00:17:25.123 --> 00:17:26.925
Haven't heard
a thing about it kid.


197
00:17:28.895 --> 00:17:30.929
This is
the only job he sent me.


198
00:17:32.164 --> 00:17:34.434
Will then I guess
you're just outta luck.


199
00:17:37.102 --> 00:17:38.604
Thanks for nothing.

200
00:17:41.674 --> 00:17:42.974
[sighs]

201
00:17:43.108 --> 00:17:45.645
[machines whirring]

202
00:17:50.450 --> 00:17:52.518
[road din]

203
00:17:53.886 --> 00:17:57.122
[plastic scraping]

204
00:18:00.959 --> 00:18:03.161
-Here let me.
-Oh, I got it.


205
00:18:13.806 --> 00:18:15.207
Thank you.

206
00:18:16.909 --> 00:18:19.311
How is
the job hunting going?


207
00:18:20.613 --> 00:18:22.147
Well, I ended up
getting fired from a job


208
00:18:22.280 --> 00:18:24.082
I never had
in the first place.


209
00:18:25.451 --> 00:18:28.053
Yeah.
Times are tough.


210
00:18:30.222 --> 00:18:31.691
Yeah, looks that way.

211
00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:38.631
Uh, have-- have
a good one, Pastor.


212
00:18:38.764 --> 00:18:41.467
[tree leaves rustling]

213
00:18:44.035 --> 00:18:45.538
If-- if you're looking
for work...


214
00:18:50.041 --> 00:18:51.444
I guess I could--

215
00:18:52.745 --> 00:18:55.046
I guess I could use
your help around here.


216
00:18:56.549 --> 00:18:59.251
Sweeping and--
and cleaning and...


217
00:19:00.419 --> 00:19:01.721
basic maintenance.

218
00:19:05.323 --> 00:19:06.792
Can't pay much...

219
00:19:09.027 --> 00:19:10.429
but maybe
it could help.


220
00:19:13.866 --> 00:19:15.200
You, uh...

221
00:19:16.502 --> 00:19:18.370
you offering me a job?

222
00:19:22.475 --> 00:19:24.510
Yeah.
It looks that way.


223
00:19:30.616 --> 00:19:31.617
Yeah.

224
00:19:31.751 --> 00:19:33.486
Okay. Sure.

225
00:19:35.721 --> 00:19:36.889
Thanks.

226
00:19:37.623 --> 00:19:40.660
So, uh, what do you
want me to do?


227
00:19:46.131 --> 00:19:47.466
[plastic scraping]

228
00:19:51.136 --> 00:19:54.339
[soft music playing]

229
00:19:57.142 --> 00:20:00.178
[trimmer buzzing]

230
00:20:24.169 --> 00:20:26.204
Hey, Dad.

231
00:20:30.776 --> 00:20:32.143
Samuel.

232
00:20:34.013 --> 00:20:35.681
Okay. Look, Samuel.
I want--


233
00:20:35.815 --> 00:20:36.916
Look, Samuel. Wait.

234
00:20:37.049 --> 00:20:38.216
[door clicks]

235
00:20:38.350 --> 00:20:40.086
[footsteps]

236
00:20:40.218 --> 00:20:41.520
Samuel. Look-- look, he--

237
00:20:41.921 --> 00:20:43.623
he came here to take care
of his mom, all right?


238
00:20:43.756 --> 00:20:45.558
-He needed a job.
-Do what you want.


239
00:20:45.691 --> 00:20:47.526
-Don't ask me to like it.
-Oh, Samuel, come on now.


240
00:20:47.660 --> 00:20:49.361
-Your mother would've wanted--
-Hey, don't do that!


241
00:20:50.261 --> 00:20:51.864
Don't even think
about doing that.


242
00:20:55.635 --> 00:20:57.268
You stay away
from me.


243
00:21:12.451 --> 00:21:15.688
["Bones" by JP Anthony playing]

244
00:21:16.389 --> 00:21:17.690
I'm sorry.

245
00:21:18.457 --> 00:21:20.291
Just another reason
to get outta here.


246
00:21:22.762 --> 00:21:24.730
Did you hear
from Brown yet?


247
00:21:25.998 --> 00:21:27.099
Not yet.

248
00:21:27.667 --> 00:21:29.702
I need a full ride
so not really an incentive


249
00:21:29.835 --> 00:21:31.037
to accept me.

250
00:21:31.804 --> 00:21:35.775
Well, at least you're majoring
in public policy.


251
00:21:37.410 --> 00:21:39.412
Gonna change the world.

252
00:21:40.479 --> 00:21:42.548
I, on the other hand,
am going to be


253
00:21:42.682 --> 00:21:45.216
a sausage cook at
the local Sizzler. [chuckles]


254
00:21:45.350 --> 00:21:47.185
The world needs
good sausage cooks.


255
00:21:47.318 --> 00:21:49.055
<i>♪ Finding my way ♪</i>

256
00:21:49.187 --> 00:21:52.257
<i>♪ But I don't know how ♪</i>

257
00:21:53.559 --> 00:21:54.860
You gonna talk to him?

258
00:21:55.795 --> 00:21:57.096
We don't talk.

259
00:21:57.228 --> 00:21:59.765
-You live in the same house.
-It's not a home though.


260
00:22:01.332 --> 00:22:02.702
Ain't been since--

261
00:22:05.370 --> 00:22:06.939
since Mom.

262
00:22:09.408 --> 00:22:10.943
Yo. Can I stay
here tonight?


263
00:22:11.077 --> 00:22:13.612
<i>♪ Nothing at all ♪</i>

264
00:22:14.714 --> 00:22:15.881
Of course.

265
00:22:16.015 --> 00:22:18.349
<i>♪ Nothing at all ♪</i>

266
00:22:18.484 --> 00:22:20.218
Come here.

267
00:22:21.520 --> 00:22:25.256
<i>♪ The more we grow ♪</i>

268
00:22:25.391 --> 00:22:27.960
<i>♪ The further we fall ♪</i>

269
00:22:29.462 --> 00:22:32.832
<i>♪ We know nothing at all ♪</i>

270
00:22:40.206 --> 00:22:43.308
[somber music playing]

271
00:22:48.279 --> 00:22:50.750
[sniffles]

272
00:22:50.883 --> 00:22:54.587
[heavy breathing]

273
00:22:54.720 --> 00:22:55.988
[grunts]

274
00:22:59.525 --> 00:23:02.828
[grunting]

275
00:23:02.962 --> 00:23:05.931
[breathing heavily]

276
00:23:13.105 --> 00:23:16.307
[yelling]

277
00:23:20.379 --> 00:23:23.516
[yelling]

278
00:23:25.384 --> 00:23:29.320
[breathing heavily]

279
00:23:31.457 --> 00:23:34.160
[cries]

280
00:23:34.727 --> 00:23:38.197
[somber music playing]

281
00:23:38.329 --> 00:23:41.000
[sipping]

282
00:23:41.133 --> 00:23:43.602
[sighs]

283
00:23:51.610 --> 00:23:54.914
[wind whooshing]

284
00:23:55.047 --> 00:23:57.983
[footsteps]

285
00:24:03.823 --> 00:24:05.724
[sighs]

286
00:24:05.858 --> 00:24:06.992
I'm sorry babe.

287
00:24:07.126 --> 00:24:10.029
I-- I've been
meaning to get here.


288
00:24:10.563 --> 00:24:14.800
It's just--
I don't forget.


289
00:24:17.069 --> 00:24:18.437
Just--

290
00:24:19.538 --> 00:24:21.607
sometimes it's hard
to remember.


291
00:24:24.109 --> 00:24:26.645
Yeah, I wanna believe
that Samuel


292
00:24:26.779 --> 00:24:28.981
comes by here
every now and again.


293
00:24:32.284 --> 00:24:33.652
I hope he does.

294
00:24:39.024 --> 00:24:40.358
I'm losing him.

295
00:24:46.432 --> 00:24:47.900
Nah, I lost him.

296
00:24:50.836 --> 00:24:53.372
I've lost him.
And I-- I don't know where.


297
00:24:58.410 --> 00:25:00.579
I promise you,
I promise you I'll--


298
00:25:02.414 --> 00:25:04.083
I will keep trying.

299
00:25:06.185 --> 00:25:10.055
In the meantime,
it seems like there's somebody


300
00:25:10.189 --> 00:25:11.657
I'm supposed to help.

301
00:25:14.093 --> 00:25:16.528
I just hope
this is what you want.


302
00:25:19.431 --> 00:25:23.135
[birds chirping]

303
00:25:42.354 --> 00:25:43.689
What are you doing?

304
00:25:45.257 --> 00:25:46.725
Light was out.

305
00:25:48.627 --> 00:25:51.597
I don't know.
Felt wrong.


306
00:25:54.133 --> 00:25:55.601
Tell you what...

307
00:25:55.734 --> 00:25:57.803
this place's in better shape

308
00:25:57.937 --> 00:26:00.105
than the chapel at Koppelman.

309
00:26:03.342 --> 00:26:05.110
Yeah. Koppelman.

310
00:26:05.244 --> 00:26:06.379
You been?

311
00:26:07.212 --> 00:26:10.582
Uh, I used to get called
out there every now and again


312
00:26:10.716 --> 00:26:13.218
before they got
a full-time chaplain.


313
00:26:13.352 --> 00:26:15.955
-[clears throat]
-[Troy] Yeah, Chaplain Kerry.


314
00:26:16.455 --> 00:26:18.557
Met with him
once or twice.


315
00:26:25.464 --> 00:26:26.799
Was it hard...

316
00:26:27.666 --> 00:26:30.736
what you did,
forgiving me?


317
00:26:34.039 --> 00:26:35.174
Yes.

318
00:26:38.344 --> 00:26:40.045
So why'd you do it?

319
00:26:40.913 --> 00:26:42.581
You think
I shouldn't have?


320
00:26:44.550 --> 00:26:46.051
[sighs]

321
00:26:50.589 --> 00:26:52.691
You know, I met
a lot of guys in there.


322
00:26:54.727 --> 00:26:56.161
Guys just like me.

323
00:26:58.664 --> 00:27:00.032
No dads...

324
00:27:01.367 --> 00:27:05.871
dropouts, screw ups.

325
00:27:10.075 --> 00:27:12.177
[sighs]

326
00:27:12.311 --> 00:27:13.512
I mean...

327
00:27:14.279 --> 00:27:18.117
maybe we don't
deserve to get out.


328
00:27:21.086 --> 00:27:25.958
Maybe we don't
deserve to be forgiven.


329
00:27:34.533 --> 00:27:36.301
God forgives.

330
00:27:41.273 --> 00:27:42.608
Yeah.

331
00:27:47.913 --> 00:27:51.784
A lot of people said
that I shouldn't.


332
00:27:54.820 --> 00:27:56.121
Lot of people...

333
00:27:57.990 --> 00:28:00.125
said you didn't get
what you deserved.


334
00:28:04.763 --> 00:28:07.166
The older I get,
I-- I realize that...


335
00:28:09.402 --> 00:28:10.869
when we don't forgive...

336
00:28:14.306 --> 00:28:16.341
we're the ones
who suffer the most.


337
00:28:20.312 --> 00:28:21.847
I've suffered enough.

338
00:28:27.420 --> 00:28:28.887
[Willis] Uh, pastor.

339
00:28:30.989 --> 00:28:35.360
Oh, hey, Willis,
um, we'll go to my office.


340
00:28:36.662 --> 00:28:38.230
Duty calls. Um--

341
00:28:39.432 --> 00:28:40.966
That there. That's good.

342
00:28:45.003 --> 00:28:47.606
What? Got something
in my teeth?


343
00:28:51.777 --> 00:28:55.114
[footsteps]

344
00:28:55.247 --> 00:28:58.518
The county's already
handling the deed transfer,


345
00:28:58.650 --> 00:29:00.786
so we're done.

346
00:29:01.286 --> 00:29:03.288
Yeah, your momma
talked about doing this


347
00:29:03.423 --> 00:29:07.527
before she passed, but
I didn't think she was serious.


348
00:29:07.659 --> 00:29:10.696
Yeah, you can
thank her someday.


349
00:29:12.664 --> 00:29:13.999
It needs
a lot of work.


350
00:29:14.633 --> 00:29:17.035
Yeah, I know.
I know.


351
00:29:23.543 --> 00:29:25.177
[grunts, sniffs]

352
00:29:25.310 --> 00:29:27.246
This is the best job
you could get?


353
00:29:29.549 --> 00:29:31.150
Guess so.

354
00:29:31.283 --> 00:29:32.784
What do you want?

355
00:29:35.220 --> 00:29:37.356
I'm just here
to take care of my mom, kid.


356
00:29:43.896 --> 00:29:45.264
How did she die?

357
00:29:51.538 --> 00:29:53.005
[Troy grunts]

358
00:29:55.207 --> 00:29:56.509
You really
want to talk about this?


359
00:29:56.643 --> 00:29:57.976
No, I don't.
But here we are.


360
00:30:00.613 --> 00:30:02.014
I wanna know
what you did.


361
00:30:03.982 --> 00:30:05.951
I wanna know
what her last breath was like.


362
00:30:07.786 --> 00:30:09.121
[sniffs]

363
00:30:14.527 --> 00:30:15.694
It was an accident.

364
00:30:15.827 --> 00:30:17.397
An accident.

365
00:30:18.797 --> 00:30:21.233
-It's true.
-Says who?


366
00:30:22.468 --> 00:30:23.769
You?

367
00:30:25.337 --> 00:30:27.507
-You don't wanna hear about it.
-Yes, I do.


368
00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:29.308
No, you don't.

369
00:30:30.809 --> 00:30:32.144
So that's it?

370
00:30:34.913 --> 00:30:36.715
Stay outta my sight...

371
00:30:39.017 --> 00:30:40.687
or I won't be responsible
for what happens.


372
00:30:40.819 --> 00:30:42.120
And who will?

373
00:30:43.255 --> 00:30:44.424
God?

374
00:30:45.592 --> 00:30:47.159
I don't believe in God.

375
00:30:49.861 --> 00:30:53.065
[somber music continues]

376
00:31:02.542 --> 00:31:04.843
[engine revving]

377
00:31:10.416 --> 00:31:13.819
What? What?
He-- he just walked out?


378
00:31:15.287 --> 00:31:17.256
No. No.
It is not like him at all.


379
00:31:17.390 --> 00:31:19.891
But hang on.
Yeah, he-- he-- he's here now.


380
00:31:20.025 --> 00:31:21.260
I'll call you back.

381
00:31:21.394 --> 00:31:22.495
Samuel.

382
00:31:22.995 --> 00:31:24.296
Excuse me!

383
00:31:24.930 --> 00:31:27.065
Samuel! Boy, turn around.

384
00:31:27.199 --> 00:31:28.300
What?

385
00:31:28.668 --> 00:31:30.369
Your principal just called.

386
00:31:30.836 --> 00:31:32.004
What'd she say?

387
00:31:32.137 --> 00:31:34.239
She said you cut today?

388
00:31:34.374 --> 00:31:35.475
Yeah?

389
00:31:37.577 --> 00:31:39.845
What is this?
What-- what are you doing?


390
00:31:39.978 --> 00:31:41.547
What are you doing?

391
00:31:44.384 --> 00:31:45.551
Okay.

392
00:31:46.519 --> 00:31:47.819
This is about Troy.

393
00:31:49.455 --> 00:31:51.123
Would you like to
come down and talk about--


394
00:31:51.256 --> 00:31:52.324
I don't.

395
00:31:56.028 --> 00:31:59.364
She's giving you a break
because you're my son.


396
00:31:59.499 --> 00:32:02.367
You cut again,
there will be consequences.


397
00:32:02.502 --> 00:32:03.935
Okay. Thank you.

398
00:32:04.069 --> 00:32:05.638
Look, Samuel,
I'm doing the best I can here.


399
00:32:05.772 --> 00:32:07.272
[door slams]

400
00:32:14.580 --> 00:32:15.947
Maureen.

401
00:32:17.049 --> 00:32:18.685
Got your autopsy report.

402
00:32:19.051 --> 00:32:20.620
Boy, are they slow.

403
00:32:20.753 --> 00:32:22.422
-Joe has the file?
-Yeah.


404
00:32:24.089 --> 00:32:26.091
It wasn't a drifter.

405
00:32:26.858 --> 00:32:28.528
Who was it?

406
00:32:29.027 --> 00:32:30.797
Why don't you
take a look?


407
00:32:30.929 --> 00:32:33.932
[ominous music playing]

408
00:32:36.669 --> 00:32:38.036
Yep.

409
00:32:40.440 --> 00:32:41.774
[Maureen] Hmm...

410
00:32:42.207 --> 00:32:44.544
[crickets chirping]

411
00:32:44.677 --> 00:32:47.413
[gravel grinding]

412
00:32:50.483 --> 00:32:52.050
[whistles]

413
00:32:56.021 --> 00:32:57.490
It's all yours?

414
00:32:58.290 --> 00:33:00.626
-Hell of a place.
-Church's.


415
00:33:03.061 --> 00:33:05.598
I'm gonna turn it
into a home


416
00:33:05.732 --> 00:33:07.232
for abused women.

417
00:33:08.468 --> 00:33:11.370
A place where they can
find a little hope.


418
00:33:14.540 --> 00:33:16.409
Needs a lot
of work, doesn't it?


419
00:33:19.044 --> 00:33:20.045
Yes, it does.

420
00:33:20.178 --> 00:33:23.516
[cheerful music playing]

421
00:33:27.886 --> 00:33:29.187
Let's go.

422
00:33:29.622 --> 00:33:30.857
Three!

423
00:33:30.989 --> 00:33:31.990
[metal clangs]

424
00:33:32.124 --> 00:33:35.894
[indistinct chatter]

425
00:33:36.027 --> 00:33:41.266
♪

426
00:34:30.516 --> 00:34:33.786
[music stops]

427
00:34:33.920 --> 00:34:35.388
[metallic clanking]

428
00:34:38.891 --> 00:34:40.325
[Troy groans]

429
00:34:45.297 --> 00:34:46.732
You-- you all right?

430
00:34:50.803 --> 00:34:54.407
Uh, yeah.
Just some old battle wounds.


431
00:34:56.843 --> 00:34:58.411
So, halfway house, huh?

432
00:35:01.414 --> 00:35:02.615
Yeah.

433
00:35:04.584 --> 00:35:06.652
That's what Elizabeth
always wanted.


434
00:35:09.889 --> 00:35:11.089
Hmm.

435
00:35:11.657 --> 00:35:13.593
She always got
what she wanted...


436
00:35:15.761 --> 00:35:17.028
sooner or later.

437
00:35:23.001 --> 00:35:24.570
What was she like?

438
00:35:27.640 --> 00:35:28.875
I'm sorry.

439
00:35:29.007 --> 00:35:31.176
-Look, I didn't mean--
-Mm-mm.


440
00:35:31.309 --> 00:35:34.614
[birds chirping]

441
00:35:40.720 --> 00:35:44.122
[heavy breathing]

442
00:35:48.694 --> 00:35:51.564
[crickets chirping]

443
00:36:06.278 --> 00:36:07.580
I didn't mean to.

444
00:36:07.713 --> 00:36:10.416
-I just--
-Our last talk...


445
00:36:12.785 --> 00:36:13.920
was a fight.

446
00:36:14.052 --> 00:36:17.055
[soft piano music playing]

447
00:36:20.927 --> 00:36:23.563
You're saying things
you don't even mean...


448
00:36:27.934 --> 00:36:30.168
and then 24 hours later,

449
00:36:30.302 --> 00:36:32.772
all you hear
are all the...


450
00:36:34.339 --> 00:36:36.207
awful things you said

451
00:36:36.341 --> 00:36:40.211
rattling around
your head like ghosts.


452
00:36:47.053 --> 00:36:48.754
And all you
have are ghosts.


453
00:36:55.795 --> 00:36:57.496
[sniffles]

454
00:36:58.564 --> 00:37:00.766
She wanted me
to take her out on a date.


455
00:37:04.470 --> 00:37:05.605
She wasn't wrong either.

456
00:37:05.738 --> 00:37:08.841
I-- I never got
that part right.


457
00:37:10.543 --> 00:37:14.179
Always spending
all my time taking care


458
00:37:14.312 --> 00:37:16.382
of everybody else
at the expense of us.


459
00:37:18.050 --> 00:37:19.418
Bad habit.

460
00:37:21.387 --> 00:37:23.154
Pastor habit.

461
00:37:29.795 --> 00:37:31.363
[sniffles]

462
00:37:31.497 --> 00:37:33.666
I'm sorry
I walked away like that.


463
00:37:36.102 --> 00:37:37.470
It's fine.

464
00:37:40.906 --> 00:37:45.176
You know what you're saying,
it's honest.


465
00:37:49.382 --> 00:37:51.817
There's something wrong
with being honest?


466
00:37:53.653 --> 00:37:57.155
People don't want
their pastors honest.


467
00:37:58.991 --> 00:38:00.559
They want 'em perfect.

468
00:38:05.998 --> 00:38:07.165
Why?

469
00:38:07.667 --> 00:38:10.670
To give 'em someone
to look up to?


470
00:38:12.905 --> 00:38:14.473
Someone to resent.

471
00:38:17.342 --> 00:38:18.644
Geez.

472
00:38:19.145 --> 00:38:20.746
Not a lot
of hope there.


473
00:38:22.782 --> 00:38:26.752
Your job
is to give them hope.


474
00:38:28.521 --> 00:38:29.855
Give them the hope.

475
00:38:30.723 --> 00:38:34.527
Where's the hope?
Don't forget the hope.


476
00:38:38.229 --> 00:38:39.799
That's what
she used to say.


477
00:38:49.408 --> 00:38:52.678
[sighing]

478
00:38:52.812 --> 00:38:54.380
I am sorry.

479
00:38:58.216 --> 00:38:59.952
I already forgave you.

480
00:39:01.587 --> 00:39:03.856
Some things
take work, you know.


481
00:39:12.965 --> 00:39:16.969
It's not the blood
you can't wash out


482
00:39:17.103 --> 00:39:18.571
you should worry about.

483
00:39:20.338 --> 00:39:22.108
It's the blood you can.

484
00:39:22.240 --> 00:39:27.480
♪

485
00:39:36.489 --> 00:39:38.991
[motorcycle revving]

486
00:39:44.630 --> 00:39:47.032
[bottles clanking]

487
00:39:47.166 --> 00:39:48.534
Don't tell Dad.

488
00:39:49.168 --> 00:39:50.268
You too.

489
00:39:50.402 --> 00:39:51.837
[laughs]

490
00:39:54.339 --> 00:39:56.509
Hey, so,
what are we celebrating?


491
00:39:58.978 --> 00:40:00.311
What?

492
00:40:00.446 --> 00:40:02.280
["Hard To Hold On"
by Pete Muller playing]


493
00:40:02.414 --> 00:40:03.983
I got a letter.

494
00:40:05.718 --> 00:40:06.585
Brown?

495
00:40:06.719 --> 00:40:09.822
Yeah. I got in.
Full ride.


496
00:40:10.422 --> 00:40:11.924
Samuel. That's--

497
00:40:13.324 --> 00:40:14.727
I know.

498
00:40:14.860 --> 00:40:17.730
<i>♪ Too hard to hold onto ♪</i>

499
00:40:18.230 --> 00:40:19.865
So what did
your dad say?


500
00:40:22.601 --> 00:40:24.335
-I'm sorry. I should--
-It-- it's okay.


501
00:40:24.470 --> 00:40:26.939
<i>♪ So hard to hold on ♪</i>

502
00:40:27.072 --> 00:40:28.440
I didn't tell him yet.

503
00:40:29.408 --> 00:40:30.576
Why not?

504
00:40:30.709 --> 00:40:32.912
Because he was
gone all day.


505
00:40:33.045 --> 00:40:34.647
Hanging out
with his new employee.


506
00:40:34.780 --> 00:40:35.848
Yep.

507
00:40:37.950 --> 00:40:41.319
<i>♪ And I need you to stay ♪</i>

508
00:40:43.222 --> 00:40:45.758
<i>♪ So hard to hold onto ♪</i>

509
00:40:45.891 --> 00:40:49.360
[bar din]

510
00:40:51.329 --> 00:40:52.898
[muttering indistinctly]

511
00:40:57.102 --> 00:40:58.671
The hell is this?

512
00:40:59.772 --> 00:41:01.307
[Troy] There a problem here?

513
00:41:01.440 --> 00:41:03.642
There wasn't one
till they let you in here.


514
00:41:04.543 --> 00:41:06.011
And why wouldn't they?

515
00:41:07.613 --> 00:41:09.114
-Clear out.
-Lay off.


516
00:41:09.248 --> 00:41:10.816
I want him outta here.

517
00:41:10.950 --> 00:41:12.818
Look, I'm just trying
to have a drink with this lo--


518
00:41:12.952 --> 00:41:14.887
I said
get the hell out!


519
00:41:15.454 --> 00:41:17.690
All right.
Both of you out!


520
00:41:21.293 --> 00:41:23.963
You know that anger
is a real problem, kid.


521
00:41:31.170 --> 00:41:32.571
You too, Samuel.

522
00:41:37.376 --> 00:41:38.510
He did his time.

523
00:41:38.644 --> 00:41:39.945
Not enough.

524
00:41:41.313 --> 00:41:42.882
Look, this side of you...

525
00:41:45.317 --> 00:41:46.552
it scares me.

526
00:41:46.685 --> 00:41:52.024
[soft music playing]

527
00:41:52.157 --> 00:41:53.425
Let me out here.

528
00:41:54.660 --> 00:41:56.996
I'll walk.
Clear my head.


529
00:41:58.664 --> 00:42:01.333
[muffled music from car radio]

530
00:42:01.467 --> 00:42:04.870
[gravel grinding]

531
00:42:08.340 --> 00:42:09.842
Here.

532
00:42:10.743 --> 00:42:13.012
My dad wants me
to stay safe.


533
00:42:13.779 --> 00:42:15.047
Anyway, just take it.

534
00:42:15.881 --> 00:42:18.450
Just in case he comes
after you or something.


535
00:42:21.153 --> 00:42:22.488
I love you.

536
00:42:23.689 --> 00:42:25.057
You shouldn't.

537
00:42:26.325 --> 00:42:27.960
[car door shuts]

538
00:42:28.627 --> 00:42:31.864
[car engine starts]

539
00:42:39.204 --> 00:42:40.839
[door clicks]

540
00:42:44.043 --> 00:42:45.644
When were you
gonna tell me?


541
00:42:46.812 --> 00:42:48.180
What you talking about?

542
00:42:49.682 --> 00:42:51.050
Full ride?

543
00:42:51.817 --> 00:42:54.586
Yeah.
Came yesterday.


544
00:42:55.521 --> 00:42:57.222
Samuel, this is
a big deal.


545
00:42:58.357 --> 00:43:01.160
I mean, it-- it is
everything you worked for.


546
00:43:02.795 --> 00:43:04.663
You didn't wanna tell me?

547
00:43:04.797 --> 00:43:07.166
You've been spending
all your time with Troy, so.


548
00:43:11.404 --> 00:43:12.838
He's playing you.

549
00:43:13.872 --> 00:43:16.443
Someday you gonna learn. Okay?

550
00:43:17.009 --> 00:43:20.312
All this anger is just gonna
rot you from the inside out.


551
00:43:20.447 --> 00:43:21.880
Okay.

552
00:43:22.915 --> 00:43:24.817
Look, Samuel,
I'm trying here.


553
00:43:28.620 --> 00:43:30.022
Thanks.

554
00:43:30.155 --> 00:43:32.624
[paper rustling]

555
00:43:36.128 --> 00:43:38.697
[birds chirping]

556
00:43:41.401 --> 00:43:42.634
[Scott]
Yep, that's right.


557
00:43:42.768 --> 00:43:44.636
The early bird
catches the worm.


558
00:43:46.238 --> 00:43:47.740
Who owns this place?

559
00:43:49.376 --> 00:43:50.809
Technically nobody.

560
00:43:51.343 --> 00:43:52.644
Technically?

561
00:43:53.446 --> 00:43:55.681
Well, this piece
of land belonged


562
00:43:55.814 --> 00:43:57.349
to the Jo Hanson family.

563
00:43:57.484 --> 00:43:58.751
Mm-hmm.

564
00:43:58.884 --> 00:44:00.953
Mary Jo Hanson
died six months ago


565
00:44:01.086 --> 00:44:03.288
and the rest of the family
left out of state.


566
00:44:04.323 --> 00:44:05.724
So who owns it now?

567
00:44:07.226 --> 00:44:09.661
Well, apparently
she gave it to the church.


568
00:44:19.204 --> 00:44:21.707
[phone rings]

569
00:44:26.446 --> 00:44:27.746
Hey, pastor.

570
00:44:28.981 --> 00:44:31.984
Oh, good.
So your phone does work.


571
00:44:33.285 --> 00:44:35.621
Yeah. Um, I'm sorry.

572
00:44:36.423 --> 00:44:38.090
Late night.
[clears throat]


573
00:44:38.824 --> 00:44:40.292
What do you
wanna do today?


574
00:44:42.661 --> 00:44:44.096
You know what?
Have a seat.


575
00:44:44.897 --> 00:44:46.565
Go on. Go on.

576
00:44:55.974 --> 00:44:58.677
Did you, uh,
did you ever pray


577
00:44:58.811 --> 00:45:01.713
with Chaplain Kerry
when you were in prison?


578
00:45:03.550 --> 00:45:06.218
He asked me to
a couple times.


579
00:45:06.351 --> 00:45:09.221
Wanted me to pray the--

580
00:45:10.089 --> 00:45:11.458
what do you call it?
The-- the--


581
00:45:11.590 --> 00:45:13.125
the sinner's prayer.

582
00:45:13.258 --> 00:45:16.195
[pensive music playing]

583
00:45:17.296 --> 00:45:18.997
But you didn't want to.

584
00:45:20.966 --> 00:45:23.335
I mean,
I know who I am.


585
00:45:23.470 --> 00:45:25.337
Don't need
to tell God.


586
00:45:29.542 --> 00:45:31.143
Yeah.

587
00:45:32.644 --> 00:45:36.215
You see,
that's the thing though.


588
00:45:39.084 --> 00:45:42.221
God already knows
who you've been.


589
00:45:45.492 --> 00:45:46.892
He wants to know...

590
00:45:48.727 --> 00:45:50.629
who do you wanna be.

591
00:45:53.533 --> 00:45:55.134
So it's a confession...

592
00:45:56.402 --> 00:45:57.803
of need...

593
00:46:01.874 --> 00:46:03.275
a request for help...

594
00:46:06.379 --> 00:46:07.679
and a pledge.

595
00:46:08.548 --> 00:46:10.215
A pledge to live different.

596
00:46:15.087 --> 00:46:17.022
All the things
you've done...


597
00:46:20.493 --> 00:46:22.027
where you've been...

598
00:46:23.996 --> 00:46:25.764
what you've seen.

599
00:46:27.199 --> 00:46:29.536
All the--
the failures and mistakes,


600
00:46:29.668 --> 00:46:31.670
those are the past.

601
00:46:31.803 --> 00:46:37.042
♪

602
00:46:38.611 --> 00:46:40.913
[dull thumping]

603
00:46:45.518 --> 00:46:47.019
[muffled scream]

604
00:46:49.422 --> 00:46:51.089
Who you've been...

605
00:46:52.991 --> 00:46:55.928
does not have to be
who you are...


606
00:47:01.300 --> 00:47:04.269
if you are willing
to believe.


607
00:47:10.410 --> 00:47:13.646
[Troy cries, sniffles]

608
00:47:13.779 --> 00:47:15.714
Will you pray with me?

609
00:47:20.886 --> 00:47:22.187
Father God...

610
00:47:24.923 --> 00:47:29.294
we come to you right now
humbled and broken.


611
00:47:31.897 --> 00:47:32.931
Thank you--

612
00:47:33.065 --> 00:47:34.701
[voice fades]

613
00:47:34.833 --> 00:47:40.239
♪

614
00:47:50.583 --> 00:47:52.918
[water splashing]

615
00:48:14.339 --> 00:48:19.278
♪

616
00:48:19.412 --> 00:48:20.446
[Troy] No kidding.

617
00:48:20.580 --> 00:48:21.980
[Marshall] Yeah. [chuckles]

618
00:48:22.114 --> 00:48:23.683
Everything he always wanted,
you know,


619
00:48:23.815 --> 00:48:27.986
a major in public policy,
learn the judicial system.


620
00:48:28.120 --> 00:48:29.855
Then you
must be proud.


621
00:48:30.556 --> 00:48:32.458
Yeah.
I am. I am.


622
00:48:32.958 --> 00:48:34.059
You tell him?

623
00:48:34.192 --> 00:48:35.728
Well, yeah, he knows.

624
00:48:35.861 --> 00:48:37.229
You know.

625
00:48:38.063 --> 00:48:39.399
You sure he knows?

626
00:48:40.500 --> 00:48:42.301
Yeah. I will--
I will make sure.


627
00:48:42.435 --> 00:48:43.536
In the meantime.

628
00:48:48.741 --> 00:48:50.075
What's this?

629
00:48:51.243 --> 00:48:54.813
It's just a-- a little
place you can call your own.


630
00:48:54.946 --> 00:48:57.450
You know, you can,
um, when you can think


631
00:48:57.583 --> 00:49:01.186
or work, whatever.

632
00:49:02.622 --> 00:49:04.890
There's also this.

633
00:49:05.023 --> 00:49:06.492
[clears throat]

634
00:49:07.159 --> 00:49:09.828
What's that?
Is that a Bible?


635
00:49:10.228 --> 00:49:11.764
Uh, it's a journal actually.

636
00:49:11.897 --> 00:49:15.100
Uh, a prayer journal.
See, you write your prayers in.


637
00:49:15.233 --> 00:49:19.004
You know, I'm not really
that good of a writer.


638
00:49:19.439 --> 00:49:22.809
Yeah, me neither.
But I-- I got a whole stack.


639
00:49:23.308 --> 00:49:26.044
So I can look back
and remember what I prayed for


640
00:49:26.178 --> 00:49:29.948
and then remember
where God showed up, so.


641
00:49:31.983 --> 00:49:34.119
Job never stops
for you, does it?


642
00:49:34.886 --> 00:49:37.222
No, it does not.
[chuckles]


643
00:49:38.857 --> 00:49:40.125
You know, come on.

644
00:49:40.258 --> 00:49:41.561
I'll give you
a ride home.


645
00:49:41.694 --> 00:49:43.463
-Yeah?
-Yeah.


646
00:49:43.596 --> 00:49:44.996
Thanks.

647
00:49:48.735 --> 00:49:50.001
[car doors slamming]

648
00:49:50.135 --> 00:49:52.871
All right.
How's your mom doing?


649
00:49:55.775 --> 00:49:56.942
She's doing all right.

650
00:49:57.075 --> 00:49:58.745
You know,
I'd see her more,


651
00:49:58.877 --> 00:50:01.046
but I got a side hustle at this
church keeping me really busy.


652
00:50:01.179 --> 00:50:03.215
-[laughs]
-Yeah.


653
00:50:03.348 --> 00:50:05.651
Yeah, I hear
that Pastor is a piece of work.


654
00:50:05.785 --> 00:50:07.487
You know, he--
he is something.


655
00:50:07.620 --> 00:50:08.721
He is something.

656
00:50:08.855 --> 00:50:10.556
[laughs]
All right.


657
00:50:11.657 --> 00:50:13.225
Let's get you home.

658
00:50:15.828 --> 00:50:18.330
Hey, thanks again
for today.


659
00:50:20.232 --> 00:50:22.702
My pleasure.
My pleasure.


660
00:50:22.835 --> 00:50:25.203
[car passing]

661
00:50:27.774 --> 00:50:30.008
[engine revving]

662
00:50:31.644 --> 00:50:33.011
[Marshall] All righty.

663
00:50:33.613 --> 00:50:36.449
Home sweet home.
Thanks for the ride.


664
00:50:36.582 --> 00:50:38.049
Yeah, of course.

665
00:50:39.519 --> 00:50:41.554
Hey, you wanna come up?
See the place?


666
00:50:42.287 --> 00:50:43.890
You know, maybe have
a beer or something?


667
00:50:44.022 --> 00:50:46.925
Uh, probably not
a beer, huh?


668
00:50:47.627 --> 00:50:49.294
N-- n-- no. [chuckles]

669
00:50:49.429 --> 00:50:51.229
-Prob-- probably not.
-You like water?


670
00:50:56.268 --> 00:50:58.471
Yeah. Water would be great.

671
00:51:02.007 --> 00:51:04.042
[car door shuts closed]

672
00:51:14.587 --> 00:51:17.255
Um, nice place.

673
00:51:18.089 --> 00:51:19.991
A little--
little small, isn't it?


674
00:51:20.760 --> 00:51:23.295
As long as I can stretch out,
I'm good.


675
00:51:24.831 --> 00:51:28.768
Uh, you didn't wanna
move back with your mom?


676
00:51:29.301 --> 00:51:32.538
Um, you know,
me and her...


677
00:51:32.672 --> 00:51:34.973
we're sort of better
with a little distance.


678
00:51:37.677 --> 00:51:38.744
[Marshall] Yeah.

679
00:51:41.046 --> 00:51:42.482
Samuel is the same way.

680
00:51:45.918 --> 00:51:47.687
Parents and kids, right?

681
00:51:49.622 --> 00:51:50.690
[sighs]

682
00:51:54.025 --> 00:51:56.228
I guess
that's why he, uh,


683
00:51:56.361 --> 00:51:58.431
why he wants to leave.

684
00:51:59.832 --> 00:52:01.132
He wants his space.

685
00:52:04.102 --> 00:52:06.104
The truth is,
he's never home


686
00:52:06.238 --> 00:52:07.507
even when he is there...

687
00:52:09.909 --> 00:52:11.176
especially lately.

688
00:52:12.778 --> 00:52:14.045
He thinks I'm--

689
00:52:14.179 --> 00:52:17.583
I'm making
a mistake with you.


690
00:52:19.785 --> 00:52:21.454
Wasting my time.

691
00:52:25.190 --> 00:52:27.292
Lonely thing
trying to save people.


692
00:52:31.597 --> 00:52:33.799
Lonelier still when
it's your own son.


693
00:52:38.638 --> 00:52:41.607
I've always been
a better pastor than a father.


694
00:52:44.410 --> 00:52:45.678
Same thing, isn't it?

695
00:52:48.146 --> 00:52:49.415
Yeah, well, he--

696
00:52:50.148 --> 00:52:53.118
he stopped listening to me
a long time ago.


697
00:52:54.987 --> 00:52:57.188
Doesn't mean
you stop trying.


698
00:52:59.659 --> 00:53:01.394
Look, pastor...

699
00:53:02.762 --> 00:53:04.262
keep the faith.

700
00:53:05.130 --> 00:53:07.800
If you don't, who will?

701
00:53:10.836 --> 00:53:12.103
[chuckles]

702
00:53:14.205 --> 00:53:16.609
Yeah, I better--
I better get going.


703
00:53:17.877 --> 00:53:19.244
[grunting]

704
00:53:28.153 --> 00:53:29.589
Don't forget to use this.

705
00:53:32.123 --> 00:53:33.459
I'll do my best.

706
00:53:34.994 --> 00:53:36.495
Good night.

707
00:53:48.841 --> 00:53:50.843
[train honking]

708
00:53:52.678 --> 00:53:53.746
[car beeps]

709
00:53:57.248 --> 00:53:58.517
[train honking]

710
00:54:00.185 --> 00:54:02.922
[car revving]

711
00:54:03.055 --> 00:54:06.058
[gravel grinding]

712
00:54:06.191 --> 00:54:11.631
♪

713
00:54:32.350 --> 00:54:33.619
[door clicks open]

714
00:54:40.059 --> 00:54:41.326
Little late, huh?

715
00:54:46.499 --> 00:54:48.233
Yeah, I guess so.

716
00:54:51.404 --> 00:54:52.738
How about you?
What did you do?


717
00:54:53.238 --> 00:54:54.573
Homework at Kaitlyn's.

718
00:54:55.841 --> 00:54:56.909
You?

719
00:54:58.544 --> 00:55:00.813
Oh, just left the church.

720
00:55:02.014 --> 00:55:03.281
You know, working late.

721
00:55:09.055 --> 00:55:10.355
Everything okay?

722
00:55:11.189 --> 00:55:12.458
It's fine.

723
00:55:13.159 --> 00:55:16.227
[ominous music plays]

724
00:55:21.834 --> 00:55:22.902
Okay.

725
00:55:23.536 --> 00:55:25.471
-See you tomorrow.
-Look...


726
00:55:27.973 --> 00:55:31.877
I-- I know you hate
what I'm doing with Troy.


727
00:55:32.011 --> 00:55:33.344
Figured that out yourself, huh?

728
00:55:33.479 --> 00:55:35.648
I'm not
asking you to understand...


729
00:55:37.383 --> 00:55:40.686
but I need you
to trust me son.


730
00:55:42.154 --> 00:55:43.422
Trust you?

731
00:55:45.191 --> 00:55:46.459
Yeah.

732
00:55:47.225 --> 00:55:48.994
He killed mom.

733
00:55:50.596 --> 00:55:52.765
-I know.
-He killed her.


734
00:55:53.331 --> 00:55:56.267
I know.

735
00:55:58.070 --> 00:55:59.370
He killed her.

736
00:56:01.006 --> 00:56:02.307
He killed her.

737
00:56:02.441 --> 00:56:04.643
-How can you just forgive?
-I can't.


738
00:56:08.180 --> 00:56:09.782
I can't.

739
00:56:11.517 --> 00:56:13.219
I never thought
I'd see him again.


740
00:56:14.319 --> 00:56:17.022
It's one thing to-- to forgive
someone from far away.


741
00:56:17.156 --> 00:56:18.924
It's another to do it

742
00:56:19.058 --> 00:56:21.927
up close day in, day out.

743
00:56:24.597 --> 00:56:25.965
But if I don't, then...

744
00:56:30.002 --> 00:56:31.470
what did she die for?

745
00:56:34.740 --> 00:56:36.307
What good comes of it?

746
00:56:37.810 --> 00:56:38.878
Nothing.

747
00:56:39.879 --> 00:56:42.815
She died so that
you could save his soul.


748
00:56:42.948 --> 00:56:45.384
Mm-mm, she died...

749
00:56:49.455 --> 00:56:52.792
and God is
giving me a chance...


750
00:56:54.527 --> 00:56:56.962
to make something
out of it.


751
00:56:59.865 --> 00:57:01.000
You too.

752
00:57:06.906 --> 00:57:07.973
Come on.

753
00:57:12.578 --> 00:57:14.914
[Samuel sobs]

754
00:57:15.047 --> 00:57:17.750
I got you. I got you.

755
00:57:17.883 --> 00:57:19.685
[Samuel sobs]

756
00:57:28.794 --> 00:57:31.564
[ominous music stops]

757
00:57:38.103 --> 00:57:39.370
[knocking on door]

758
00:57:40.005 --> 00:57:41.240
About that time.

759
00:57:41.807 --> 00:57:43.375
Well, there's no such thing
as that time


760
00:57:43.509 --> 00:57:45.110
-when you are a pastor.
-[chuckles]


761
00:57:47.079 --> 00:57:48.514
Ever wish there was?

762
00:57:48.647 --> 00:57:50.249
Just about every time
I look at my paycheck.


763
00:57:50.382 --> 00:57:51.817
-[chuckles]
-Oh.


764
00:57:54.220 --> 00:57:55.588
You-- you gonna be
all right getting home?


765
00:57:55.721 --> 00:57:57.923
Uh, yeah.
I'll be all right.


766
00:57:59.124 --> 00:58:00.826
You gonna be
all right getting home?


767
00:58:01.760 --> 00:58:03.395
-I'll be all right.
-[chuckles]


768
00:58:03.529 --> 00:58:04.864
All right.

769
00:58:05.363 --> 00:58:06.632
All right.

770
00:58:06.765 --> 00:58:07.933
[laughs]

771
00:58:08.366 --> 00:58:09.869
Have a good night, pastor.

772
00:58:10.302 --> 00:58:11.570
Yeah, you too, Troy.

773
00:58:14.039 --> 00:58:15.107
You too.

774
00:58:16.141 --> 00:58:17.409
[chuckles]

775
00:58:33.292 --> 00:58:36.462
[car revving]

776
00:58:42.167 --> 00:58:44.970
[ominous music plays]

777
00:58:46.972 --> 00:58:48.040
[Samuel] Hey.

778
00:58:51.543 --> 00:58:52.711
Get in.

779
00:58:52.845 --> 00:58:57.883
♪

780
00:59:06.558 --> 00:59:07.826
[Troy]
Thanks for the ride.


781
00:59:13.132 --> 00:59:16.168
[car revving]

782
00:59:23.475 --> 00:59:25.611
[bell ringing]

783
00:59:25.744 --> 00:59:29.481
[train honking]

784
00:59:31.684 --> 00:59:34.053
[gravel grinding]

785
00:59:36.488 --> 00:59:41.226
[train horn blaring]

786
00:59:43.095 --> 00:59:44.997
Your dad told me about Brown.

787
00:59:46.899 --> 00:59:49.068
You must be really excited
to get outta here...


788
00:59:50.669 --> 00:59:51.770
just like I was.

789
00:59:51.904 --> 00:59:53.672
I'm nothing like you.

790
00:59:55.808 --> 00:59:57.242
We're all the same, kid.

791
00:59:59.478 --> 01:00:00.779
We've all sinned.

792
01:00:01.914 --> 01:00:03.649
That's what
your dad taught me.


793
01:00:10.055 --> 01:00:11.623
[sighs]

794
01:00:12.257 --> 01:00:16.228
[bell ringing]

795
01:00:22.634 --> 01:00:23.902
It was quick.

796
01:00:26.572 --> 01:00:27.840
What?

797
01:00:28.774 --> 01:00:32.945
Your mother,
how it happened.


798
01:00:36.882 --> 01:00:38.684
That was the worst part...

799
01:00:42.287 --> 01:00:43.756
she didn't fight it.

800
01:00:47.860 --> 01:00:50.195
I held her
in my arms as she died.


801
01:00:51.997 --> 01:00:53.866
Bleeding out
all over your floor.


802
01:01:00.172 --> 01:01:01.640
[inhales deeply]

803
01:01:01.774 --> 01:01:03.376
It was
supposed to be quick.


804
01:01:03.976 --> 01:01:05.878
Just a little
smash-and-grab.


805
01:01:06.645 --> 01:01:08.080
I didn't think
anyone was home...


806
01:01:13.118 --> 01:01:14.953
then she came
into the kitchen.


807
01:01:17.823 --> 01:01:19.958
I got scared I-
- I fired.

808
01:01:27.699 --> 01:01:30.903
I'll never forget
